We have a part time position open for an AR15 Armorer. Business has picked up and we are behind on orders. We are looking for someone who is knowledgeable in every aspect of AR15's. 1. Ability to assemble complete uppers.
2. Ability to assemble complete lowers. 
3. Knowledge of Barrels including types of steel, treatments, gas port size, profile differences etc.

5. Knowledge of Bolt Carrier Groups and every component used to make them function.
6. Knowledge of every part of a lower parts kit.
7. Knowledge of stocks, springs, buffers etc.
8. Knowledge of triggers.
9. Knowledge of aftermarket parts available.

We will need someone to assemble complete uppers and lowers, assemble parts, change parts on existing firearms, trouble shoot problems if they arise, headspace and test fire the uppers and lowers. Packaging and shipping may also be needed.

This position will start off requiring approximately 4 hours per day. Total hours will depend on the volume of orders we receive. Hours worked are flexible provided they are between 9am and 4pm. Full Name

Hourly Wage Requirement

title: For Sale:  Looking to Hire - AR15 Armorer in Charlotte, NC
postcontent:
We have a part time position open for an AR15 Armorer. Business has picked up and we are behind on orders. We are looking for someone who is knowledgeable in every aspect of AR15's. Additional knowledge of AK47, Ruger 10/22, Glock and 1911 platforms will put you to the top of the list. Simply owning an AR and having the ability to clean it does NOT qualify you. 

Requirements are:
1. Ability to assemble complete uppers.
2. Ability to assemble complete lowers. 
3. Knowledge of Barrels including types of steel, treatments, gas port size, profile differences etc. 
4. Knowledge of Gas Systems.
5. Knowledge of Bolt Carrier Groups and every component used to make them function.
6. Knowledge of every part of a lower parts kit.
7. Knowledge of stocks, springs, buffers etc.
8. Knowledge of triggers.
9. Knowledge of aftermarket parts available.

We will need someone to assemble complete uppers and lowers, assemble parts, change parts on existing firearms, trouble shoot problems if they arise, headspace and test fire the uppers and lowers. Packaging and shipping may also be needed.

This position will start off requiring approximately 4 hours per day. Total hours will depend on the volume of orders we receive. Hours worked are flexible provided they are between 9am and 4pm. Hours will increase as our business continues to grow. This position could very well become a permanent full time position, sales position or even a management position for the right person. 

Our shop is located in Charlotte. We are moving to a new facility 11/1/2013. No felony convictions or anyone with a record. Please send ALL of the following to be considered:

Full Name
Phone Number
Address
Work History / Experience
Hourly Wage Requirement

Thank You.

title: For Sale:  UZI 9mm carbine and extras
postcontent:
Better than new Uzi carbine.  I've owned it for about 1 year and have run 300-400 rounds through it, so it's well "broken in".  Vector (the builder) recommends around 500 rounds.

First made in Israil, the Uzi was also made in South Africa and Germany.  When banned from import, a US company bought up all of the parts stored in those countries, and others, and starting building them here.  That company (Action arms) went out of business and the present builder is Vector Arms, of Utah.  My gun came with a German submachine gun "lower", so the fire selector is marked "D E S", for full auto, semi-auto and safe in German.  The full auto function is blocked off.

I built the gun to may taste, but have all of the stock pieces to return it to "factory".

I've added a verticle front hand grip, which was a later modification made to the submachine gun to provide better control.  On the side of the grip is a small section of Magpul rail, which allows for the installation of a lazer or flashlight (not included).

The factory bolt handle has been replaced with a small horizontal one, which doesn't tear your hand up like the original.  In addition to the folding metal stock I also have the wooden stock, which was designed for the submachine gun.

Other extras include:  9 factory 32 round magazines in three IDF (Israeli Defense Force) canvas pouches.  Other IDF items include a factory front sight adjustment tool, a magazine loading tool, a magazine "coupler" for quicker mag changes.  Other items include the original front grip, bolt handle, spare magazine release w/ spring, handgrip screws, and barrel release lever spring.

An Uncle Mikes range bag is included, along with about 550 rounds of 9mm ammo.

Buyer must be over 21 and provide AZ ID.  Prefer CCW.  Some handgun trades considered plus cash: Kimber, Colt, Sig.
